<p>The renowned Polish piano duo Marek and Wacek didn&rsquo;t use sheet music when playing live concerts. And yet onstage the pair appeared perfectly in sync. On adjacent pianos, they playfully picked up various musical themes, blended classical music with jazz and improvised in real time. &ldquo;We went with the flow,&rdquo; said Marek Tomaszewski, who performed with Wacek Kisielewski until Wacek&rsquo;s death in 1986.</p>
